### Cognee GraphRAG API (PRODUCTION)
# ⚠️  WARNING: These requests target the PRODUCTION environment
# Production URL: https://pipeline-api.felixtek.cloud/api/v1
# Use with caution - modifications affect live data
#
# Cognee provides local knowledge graph capabilities using Neo4j + pgvector
# Features: Entity extraction, graph search, hybrid retrieval, and knowledge graph statistics
#
# Prerequisites:
# - Documents must be processed with destination_type: "cognee_local"
# - Neo4j must be running and accessible
# - Environment variables: NEO4J_URI, NEO4J_USER, NEO4J_PASSWORD
#
# Valid search_types: "hybrid" (default), "graph", "vector"
# NOTE: "summary" and "chunks" search types are NOT implemented - use "graph" instead

@baseUrl = https://pipeline-api.felixtek.cloud/api/v1
@apiKey = your-api-key


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. GRAPH SEARCH
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Cognee Search - Hybrid Mode (Recommended)
# Combines vector similarity with graph traversal for comprehensive results
# Returns: content, entities[], source_document, score
POST {{baseUrl}}/cognee/search
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "query": "What are the main components of neural network architecture?",
  "search_type": "hybrid",
  "dataset_id": "default",
  "top_k": 5
}

### Cognee Search - Real Example (Relationship Query)
# Query about relationships between entities
POST {{baseUrl}}/cognee/search
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "query": "What's the relationship between Caio and Felipe?",
  "search_type": "hybrid",
  "dataset_id": "tee34",
  "top_k": 5
}

### Cognee Search - Vector Mode
# Pure vector similarity search using pgvector embeddings
# Faster but less context than hybrid
POST {{baseUrl}}/cognee/search
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "query": "machine learning applications in healthcare",
  "search_type": "vector",
  "dataset_id": "default",
  "top_k": 5
}

### Cognee Search - Graph Mode
# Graph traversal search following entity relationships
# Best for: Exploring connections between concepts
POST {{baseUrl}}/cognee/search
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "query": "Find all documents related to Kubernetes and Docker",
  "search_type": "graph",
  "dataset_id": "default",
  "top_k": 5
}


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 2. ENTITY EXTRACTION
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Extract Entities from Text
# Extract named entities and their relationships from provided text
# Uses LLM for entity recognition
POST {{baseUrl}}/cognee/extract-entities
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "text": "Google Cloud Platform provides machine learning services through Vertex AI. Kubernetes orchestrates containerized applications across clusters.",
  "dataset_id": "default"
}

### Extract Entities - Real World Example
POST {{baseUrl}}/cognee/extract-entities
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "text": "Microsoft was founded by Bill Gates and Paul Allen in 1975. It is headquartered in Redmond, Washington.",
  "dataset_id": "test-dataset"
}


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 3. KNOWLEDGE GRAPH STATISTICS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get Knowledge Graph Statistics
# Retrieve statistics about the knowledge graph structure
# Returns: total_nodes, total_relationships, entity_count, document_count
GET {{baseUrl}}/cognee/stats?dataset_id=default
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

### Get Stats for Specific Dataset
GET {{baseUrl}}/cognee/stats?dataset_id=tee34
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 4. ADVANCED SEARCH EXAMPLES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Multi-hop Query - Finding Related Concepts
# Uses graph traversal to find indirect relationships
POST {{baseUrl}}/cognee/search
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "query": "How does Docker relate to microservices architecture and container orchestration?",
  "search_type": "graph",
  "dataset_id": "default",
  "top_k": 10
}

### Complex Business Query
POST {{baseUrl}}/cognee/search
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "query": "What are the revenue implications of cloud migration strategies for enterprise companies?",
  "search_type": "hybrid",
  "dataset_id": "business-reports",
  "top_k": 5
}

### Search Type Comparison
# Use these to compare results across search types

# HYBRID (Recommended) - Best overall results
POST {{baseUrl}}/cognee/search
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "software architecture patterns",
  "dataset_id": "default",
  "search_type": "hybrid",
  "top_k": 3
}

###

# GRAPH - Best for entity relationships
POST {{baseUrl}}/cognee/search
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "software architecture patterns",
  "dataset_id": "default",
  "search_type": "graph",
  "top_k": 3
}

###

# VECTOR - Fastest, pure semantic
POST {{baseUrl}}/cognee/search
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "software architecture patterns",
  "dataset_id": "default",
  "search_type": "vector",
  "top_k": 3
}

